789
00:42:27,321 --> 00:42:31,340
Rym: If you want to adjourn the meeting, you say this, I move that we adjourn.

790
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:32,636
Rym: May you interrupt the speaker?

791
00:42:32,738 --> 00:42:32,860
Rym: No.

792
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:33,775
Rym: Must you be seconded?

793
00:42:33,836 --> 00:42:34,000
Rym: Yes.

794
00:42:34,122 --> 00:42:34,935
Rym: Is the motion debatable?

795
00:42:34,956 --> 00:42:34,996
Rym: No.

796
00:42:35,700 --> 00:42:36,593
Rym: What vote is required?

797
00:42:36,654 --> 00:42:37,080
Rym: Majority.

798
00:42:37,901 --> 00:42:39,172
Rym: So you just look at this like, what do I want to do?

799
00:42:39,192 --> 00:42:40,080
Rym: I want to amend a motion.

800
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:43,739
Rym: You find the row, you go down, you figure out if you can interrupt, and then you do it.

801
00:42:45,884 --> 00:42:47,699
Scott: What are the things you can do that allow interrupting?

802
00:42:48,362 --> 00:42:57,380
Rym: Oh, so you can interrupt the speaker to a point of privilege, so complaining about something, like something meta, like the room's too hot, I'm tired.

803
00:42:57,941 --> 00:42:58,706
Scott: Okay.

804
00:42:58,726 --> 00:43:03,980
Rym: There's no vote, it doesn't mean anything, you just, point of privilege, I'm bored.

805
00:43:06,086 --> 00:43:06,295
Scott: Nice.

806
00:43:07,461 --> 00:43:11,720
Rym: I guess I could cite you for, you know, if you use that in an insulting manner.

807
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:14,120
Scott: Point of privilege, the air conditioner is not on, I'm melting in here.

808
00:43:14,361 --> 00:43:19,080
Rym: You can object to procedure or personal affront as a point of order.

809
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:21,639
Scott: As you take personal affront, just boring shit.

810
00:43:23,184 --> 00:43:25,240
Scott: I take that as personal affront, good sir.

811
00:43:25,660 --> 00:43:33,340
Rym: Yeah, the problem is, you can interrupt the speaker, but there's no vote, the chair just handles your affront however he or she wishes.

812
00:43:34,342 --> 00:43:35,080
Scott: I'll keep affronting.

813
00:43:35,841 --> 00:43:41,994
Rym: You can call for a point of information, where you, you know, I would like to know the rule of Robert's rule of order in this case, because I don't know it.

814
00:43:42,903 --> 00:43:46,400
Rym: You can object to the consideration of an undiplomatic vote.

815
00:43:48,625 --> 00:43:49,737
